data['Gender'] = [1 if x == 'Female' 
                  else 0 
                  for x in data['Gender']]

data['CAEC'] = [0 if x == 'no' 
                else 1 if x == 'Sometimes' 
                else 2 if x == 'Frequently' 
                else 3 for x in data['CAEC']]

data['CALC'] = [0 if x == 'no'
                else 1 if x == 'Sometimes' 
                else 2 if x == 'Frequently' 
                else 3 for x in data['CALC']]

data['MTRANS'] = [0 if x == 'Automobile' 
                  else 1 if x == 'Motorbike' 
                  else 2 if x == 'Public_Transportation' 
                  else 3 if x == 'Bike'
                  else 4 for x in data['MTRANS']]

Regression Models¶

Linear Regression¶

In [166]:
kf = KFold(n_splits = 10, shuffle=True, random_state=random)

mses = []
coefs = []
scores = []

for idxtrain, idxtest in kf.split(x):
  xtrain = x[idxtrain]
  ytrain = y[idxtrain]
  xtest = x[idxtest]
  ytest = y[idxtest]

  scale = QuantileTransformer(n_quantiles=9, random_state = random)

  xstrain = scale.fit_transform(xtrain)
  xstest = scale.transform(xtest)

  linear = LinearRegression(fit_intercept=True)

  linear.fit(xstrain, ytrain)
  yhat = linear.predict(xstest)

  mses.append(mse(ytest, yhat))
  scores.append(r2_score(yhat, ytest))
  coefs.append(linear.coef_)

model_name = 'Linear Regression'
coefs_mean = np.mean(coefs, axis=0)
mses_mean = np.mean(mses)
scores_mean = np.mean(scores)
print("Mean Squared Error: ", mses_mean)
print("Mean R^2: ", scores_mean)

Mean Squared Error:  255.41675658571904
Mean R^2:  0.22607185569214333
In [167]:
eval_df.loc[model_name, 'mse'] = mses_mean
eval_df.loc[model_name, 'r2'] = scores_mean

wscale = StandardScaler()
coefs_mean_scaled = wscale.fit_transform(np.abs(coefs_mean).reshape(-1,1))

for i, name in enumerate(cols):
  weight_df.loc[model_name, name] = coefs_mean[i]

for i, name in enumerate(cols):
  weight_df_scaled.loc[model_name, name] = coefs_mean_scaled[i][0]

xscaled = scale.fit_transform(x)

for a in alphas:

    ridge.fit(xscaled, y)

def R2(y_true,y_pred):    
     r2 = r2_score(y_true, y_pred)
     print('R2: %2.3f' % r2)
     return r2

def r2_max():
    return make_scorer(r2_score, greater_is_better=True)

KFold¶

In [191]:
kf = KFold(n_splits = 10, shuffle=True, random_state=random)

mses = []
scores = []
coefs = []

for idxtrain, idxtest in kf.split(x):
  xtrain = x[idxtrain]
  ytrain = y[idxtrain]
  xtest = x[idxtest]
  ytest = y[idxtest]

  scale = QuantileTransformer(n_quantiles=9, random_state = random)

  xstrain = scale.fit_transform(xtrain)
  xstest = scale.transform(xtest)

  n = 9

  gam = LinearGAM(n_splines=n)

  gam.fit(xstrain, ytrain)
  yhat = gam.predict(xstest)
  mses.append(mse(ytest, yhat))
  scores.append(r2_score(yhat, ytest))

  c = gam.coef_[1:].reshape(15,n)
  coefs.append(np.max(c, axis=1))

model_name = 'LinearGAM'
coefs_mean = np.abs(np.mean(coefs, axis=0))
mses_mean = np.mean(mses)
scores_mean = np.mean(scores)
print("Mean Squared Error: ", mses_mean)
print("Mean R^2: ", scores_mean)

Mean Squared Error:  216.78367095853986
Mean R^2:  0.4276073470256754

KFold¶

In [195]:
kf = KFold(n_splits = 10, shuffle=True, random_state=random)

mses = []
scores = []
coefs = []

for idxtrain, idxtest in kf.split(x):
  xtrain = x[idxtrain]
  ytrain = y[idxtrain]
  xtest = x[idxtest]
  ytest = y[idxtest]

  scale = QuantileTransformer(n_quantiles=9, random_state = random)

  xstrain = scale.fit_transform(xtrain)
  xstest = scale.transform(xtest)

  rf = RandomForestRegressor(n_estimators=43, random_state=random)

  rf.fit(xstrain, ytrain)
  yhat = rf.predict(xstest)

  mses.append(mse(ytest, yhat))
  scores.append(r2_score(yhat, ytest))
  coefs.append(rf.feature_importances_)

model_name = 'Random Forest'
coefs_mean = np.mean(coefs, axis=0)
mses_mean = np.mean(mses)
scores_mean = np.mean(scores)
print("Mean Squared Error: ", mses_mean)
print("Mean R^2: ", scores_mean)

kf = KFold(n_splits = 10, shuffle=True, random_state=random)

mses = []
scores = []
coefs = []

for idxtrain, idxtest in kf.split(x):
  xtrain = x[idxtrain]
  ytrain = y[idxtrain]
  xtest = x[idxtest]
  ytest = y[idxtest]

  scale = QuantileTransformer(n_quantiles=9, random_state = random)

  xstrain = scale.fit_transform(xtrain)
  xstest = scale.transform(xtest)

  xgt = xgb.XGBRegressor(booster='gbtree', eta=0.59, gamma=13.25)

  xgt.fit(xstrain, ytrain)
  yhat = xgt.predict(xstest)

  scores.append(r2_score(yhat, ytest))
  coefs.append(xgt.feature_importances_)

model_name = 'XGBoost Tree'
